2021 SIERRA RX3 Spec sheet

195HP 1300cc Suzuki Hayabusa Engine With Dynojet powercommander (91 Oct)
High volume oil pump, high capacity aluminum oil pan, billet oil cooler adaptor
6-Speed Sequential transmission
Sadev gear transfer system including reverse, quick change gear ratios, adjustable LSD, Internal gear oil pump
100% Made in America DOM steel chassis
4-Wheel 10.3” Vented disc rotors 
Wilwood 4 piston Calipers
Wilwood pedal box adjustable brake bias and dual master cylinders 
Stainless braided brake lines
Axle driven alternator 
PRP window nets
RCV Axles 
Exit 2-Way adjustable shocks w/12” wheel travel front & rear
AIM MXM display and data logger
Fuel level sensor 
APR carbon wing
Sabelt GT-Pad Halo seat 
Sabelt 6pt harnesses 
Sabelt steering wheel
C&R radiator and oil coolers
SPAL fan
Radium fuel system 
Powder coated aluminum body with dzus tabs
Electric assist power steering
Billet steering rack with adjustable ratios
Hydraulic wilwood hand brake
SPA On board fire system
Billet engine & gearbox mounts
Steel-It coated chassis
Aluminum fuel cell (4.8 gallons)
Billet front rotor hats
Billet rear hubs
14” OZ Rally wheels 
Lexan windshield 
Adjustable/collapsible steering column 
Splined adjustable sway bars

AK Pikes Peak demo additional options
HD Pikes Peak cooling system
Fully Enclosed aluminum rear bulkhead and harness covers
Oracle triple headlights
Stiffer rear springs 
Stiffer front spring
Big tire (30-32”)gear ratios

Wheelbase 94”

Total weight 1150lbs

17’ platinum LCG (low center of gravity) #f250 we built back in 2017. 40” tires no “lift” …. The nose is 2” higher or leveled. The rear is stock height but with a progressive pack and deleted the factory block. This truck has glass fenders front and rear 4” per side.  In my opinion this is the best way to have a big truck on big tires. I’ve done ram 2500 with the same treatment and absolutely in love with how well this works, drives and looks. #f250 #f350

node.text: A few weeks back during peak week on an off day I blasted out to #pensylvania to go to the #gmnationals for the day. The experience was unexpectedly very rad. Of course all the people I met were very sweet and we had a great time talking about all sorts of things but a real prize for me was having @racelance drive me around the fairgrounds in this 1960 #24hoursoflemans class winner. At which time he told me about his farther and his love of corvettes and passion to find this one. The epic journey of this little car can not be understated. When it comes to car collecting I am most fascinated with race cars… every time they left the grid not only was the machine wagered but many times the life of the pilot. After much struggle and painful effort John Fitch pulled off the win. This car was lost!…then reeled back out of the abyss by Chip Miller with dreams of it taking the track at Le Mans …again….. sadly Chip wouldn’t see this day but Lance would see the task through and with John at the wheel 50 years later this little car from America returned to that hallowed ground. Lance supplied me with a copy of the documentary just as I was out the door headed back to Colorado for the hill climb. That night after the race my homie @bobthetrackguy and I popped it in and after a day racing we watched films about racing and I enjoyed every minute. So if you’re into the same crap as me I think this was such a great story about a wonderful piece of racing history. Enjoy ❤️
